Drain the @firm tofu{280%g} and chop into 2cm cubes. Pat dry with #kitchen paper{}, then pop into a large #bowl{} and set aside.

Peel and grate the @garlic clove{1}(peeled and grated) (or use a #garlic press{}).

Trim and peel the @carrot{1}. Use the #peeler{} to peel long ribbons down the length of the carrot, stopping at the core.

Pour the @water{300%ml} for the rice and @salt{1/4%tsp} into a medium #saucepan{} with a tight-fitting #lid{}.

Stir in the @jasmine rice{150%g} and bring to the boil. Once boiling, turn the heat down to medium and cover with the lid.

Leave to cook for ~{10%minutes}, then remove the pan from the heat (still covered) and leave to the side for another ~{10%minutes} or until ready to serve (the rice will continue to cook in its own steam).

Meanwhile, pop the carrot ribbons into a small bowl with the @rice vinegar{15%ml} and @sugar{1/2%tsp} for the pickle.

Add a pinch of @?salt{pinch}, mix together and set aside.

Halve any thick @tenderstem broccoli{80%g} stems lengthways. Heat a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle} in a medium #frying pan{} on medium-high heat.

Once hot, add the broccoli and stir-fry for ~{2-3%minutes}.

Add the garlic and cook until fragrant, ~{30%seconds}, then add a splash of @water{1%splash}. Cover with a #lid{} (or foil), then allow to cook until tender, ~{2-3%minutes} more.

Season with @salt{pinch} and @pepper{pinch}, then transfer to a bowl and cover to keep warm.

Pop the (now empty) frying pan back on high heat with a drizzle of @oil{1%drizzle}.

Once hot, fry the tofu until slightly crispy, ~{8-10%minutes}. Turn frequently to ensure it doesn't burn.

Once golden, sprinkle over the @Indonesian style spice mix{1}. Stir-fry for ~{30%seconds}, then pour in the @bulgogi sauce{150%g}, @sambal paste{15%g} (add less if you'd prefer things milder) and half the @soy sauce{15%ml}. Stir to combine.

Bring to the boil, then reduce the heat and simmer until slightly thickened, ~{1%minute}. Add a splash of @water{1%splash} if it's a little thick, then remove from the heat.

When everything's ready, fluff up the rice with a #fork{} and stir through the remaining @soy sauce{15%ml}. Share the rice between your bowls.

Top your rice with the garlic broccoli, spicy tofu and pickled carrot in separate sections.

Sprinkle over the @roasted white sesame seeds{5%g} to finish. Enjoy!

> This recipe serves 2 people. Adjust ingredient quantities accordingly for different serving sizes.

> Sambal paste can be adjusted to taste depending on how mild or spicy you prefer.